,{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"directory.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How Snapshots Work","anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The VM "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"must be stopped","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" before saving or restoring."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the snapshot copies."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write","text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FileManager.copyItem"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which the system maps to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"clonefile(2)"},{"type":"text","text":". This produces a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consume additional storage."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout","t